Legislative Document No. 231
H.P. 154 House of Representatives, January 21, 2025
An Act to Update the Solid Waste Management Hierarchy
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 16, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant
to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CAMPBELL of Orrington.
Cosponsored by Senator HAGGAN of Penobscot and
Representatives: DILL of Old Town, GREENWOOD of Wales, SOBOLESKI of Phillips.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 38 MRSA ยง2101, sub-ยง1, as amended by PL 2007, c. 583, ยง7, is further
3 amended to read:
4 1. Priorities. It is the policy of the State to plan for and implement an integrated
5 approach to solid waste management for solid waste generated in this State and solid waste
6 imported into this State, which must be based on the following order of priority:
7 A. Reduction of waste generated at the source, including both amount and toxicity of
8 the waste;
9 B. Reuse of waste;
10 B-1. Waste processing that reduces the volume of waste needing land disposal,
11 including incineration;
12 C. Recycling of waste;
13 D. Composting of biodegradable waste; and
14 E. Waste processing that reduces the volume of waste needing land disposal, including
15 incineration; and
16 F. Land disposal of waste.
17 It is the policy of the State to use the order of priority in this subsection as a guiding
18 principle in making decisions related to solid waste management.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This bill changes the policy of the State related to the integrated approach to solid waste
2211 management by increasing the priority of waste processing that reduces the volume of
2222 waste needing land disposal, including incineration, from the 5th priority of solid waste
2233 management to the 3rd priority.
